There could be several approaches to resolving this task:

1. A list of lists/arrays should be used to store a pair of the input lines:
```java
public static void reverseBlock(BufferedReader r, PrintWriter w) throws IOException {
    List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    String line;
    List&lt;String&gt; pair = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    while ((line = r.readLine()) != null) {
        pair.add(line);
        if (pair.size() == 2) {
            list.add(pair);
            pair = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        }
    }
    if (!pair.isEmpty()) { // check for an odd number of lines in the input
        list.add(pair);
    }
    Collections.reverse(list);
    for (List&lt;String&gt; p : list) {
        for (String text : p) {
            w.println(text);
        }
    }
}
```
2. Use method `List::add(int index, E element)` to insert lines in appropriate order.

The approach above is overly excessive and a simpler way should be used.

If we look at the order of insertion of the initial data, we can see that the elements should be inserted in this way:
```java
list.add(0, &quot;cat&quot;);   // [&quot;cat&quot;]
list.add(1, &quot;dog&quot;);   // [&quot;cat&quot;, &quot;dog&quot;]
list.add(0, &quot;bunny&quot;); // [&quot;bunny&quot;, &quot;cat&quot;, &quot;dog&quot;]
list.add(1, &quot;fish&quot;);  // [&quot;bunny&quot;, &quot;fish&quot;, &quot;cat&quot;, &quot;dog&quot;]
...
```
So the entire method could be rewritten as:
```java
public static void reverseBlock(BufferedReader r, PrintWriter w) throws IOException {
    List&lt;String&gt; list = new LinkedList&lt;&gt;();
    String line;
    while ((line = r.readLine()) != null) {
        list.add(list.size() % 2, line);
    }

    for (String text : list) {
        w.println(text);
    }
}
```
Here `list.size() % 2` provides a sequence of `0, 1, 0, 1` without extra counter / loop.  Also, `LinkedList` should be used here because it should have better performance when inserting elements at the head of the list.

